{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YZDMUcvKg31pCX33An5yKL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's what was wrong and what I fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had only `write` and `read` permissions on the `/app` vhost — the `configure` permission was empty. RabbitMQ requires `configure` permission to declare (create) a queue, so the producer's `PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` call was refused with \"Access refused.\"\n\n**Fix:** Granted full permissions to `app-user` on `/app`:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Result:**\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running` with 0 restarts\n- `/app` vhost contains `app-queue` of type `classic` (durable) with 36 messages and counting\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes remain `Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":248,"cache_read_input_tokens":33702,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":248},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0ba6544-1ae2-419b-a7f4-95a6f19fcf01","uuid":"6944f251-9f2b-470c-b7ae-3b906188bc13","request_id":"req_011CcMPdWAnV4LBQP2SG6xuz"}
